SIMPLE: inquisitor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Inquisitor
<hw>In*quis"i*tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.: cf. F.
<ets>inquisiteur</ets>. See <er>Inquire</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>An
inquisitive person; one fond of asking questions.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Inquisitors</xex> are tatlers.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Feltham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>One whose official duty it is to
examine and inquire, as coroners, sheriffs, etc.</def> <rj><au>Mozley &
W.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(R.C.Ch.)</fld> <def>A member of the Court of
Inquisition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Inquisitorial</ent>⟦br⟧
